{"word":"δύσφρων","slug":"δύσφρων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δύσφρων</b></el> <el>(δύς-φρων, ονος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φρήν'><el>φρήν</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>sad at heart, sorrowful, melancholy</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>ill-disposed, malignant</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b>= <a href='S:ἄφρων'><el>ἄφρων</el></a>, <i>insensate</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}